item.title: Portforwarding problem, say's online but don't connect!
item.dc:creator: @Crysis_v2 Crysis_v2
item.description:
@Crysis_v2 wrote:

Okay, many people have problems doing this… it’s simple.
First off open up a cmd.
(Go to your start panel, type in “cmd”)
Now type in “ipconfig.” Look for you’re IP address and default gateway.
Once you have those, open up your internet browser and type in your default gateway in the address bar.
A window should pop up, this is normal.

Depending on your connection, you need username and password credentials to log into router.
Most username and password credentials are:
Username: Admin
Password: Admin
Otherwise you’ll have to ask a parent or get the credentials yourself, considering you’re probably still young and you have a setup internet connection.

Once you get into your router setup and have successfully logged in, there should be some tabs. Look for a tab labeled “Applications & Gaming” or something of that sort. Once there, there should be six port range columns. The first one should be labeled “application” or something of that sort. It’s hard to determine because we might not have the same router system. Label the “application” box RSPS. The next two boxes should start and end ports. Label them with “43594”
Your next step is to set the protocol box to “both” and finish the process by setting the IP address column with the last three digits of your IP (your IP can be found under the “ipconfig” process using the CMD, as stated above)
Once thats done, enable everything by checking the enable box on the last column and proceed on to saving your settings.

Next, create a no-ip account.
http://www.no-ip.com/

Once done, add a host and save your settings for that.
After that, download the NO-IP DUC client here: https://www.no-ip.com/downloads.php
Once installed, open the DUC and log in to it using your no-ip username and password.
Once done, select the host you created on the website by checking the box in the DUC and saving.
That’s about all there is to it.
If you need any further assistance, message me.
Hope this helped!
